						<summary>

						<p>A fragmentary slab built into the platform in front of Āñjanēya temple.</p>						

						<p>ACHYUTADĒVARĀYA.</p>						

						<p>1542 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka [1]464, Śōbhakṛit, Pushya, śu. 9, corresponding to December 17, Friday-Saturday 1542 A.D. The tithi is sūrya-tithi.</p>						

						<p>Incomplete and fragmentary. Refers to the service of soldier (bamṭu koluvu) of Chiṁnnama nāyaka son of Rāvulanāyaka. It also refers to Chaṁnūri sīma, the nāyaṁkara of Veṁgala rāju, son of Tirumalurāju.</p>						

						</summary>
